6652   // Strip cast operations from a pointer value.
6653   // Note that stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation can strip off getelementptr
6654   // inbounds with zero offset. To guarantee that the result isn't poison, the
6655   // stripped pointer is checked as it has to be pointing into an allocated
6656   // object or be null `null` to ensure `inbounds` getelement pointers with a
6657   // zero offset could not produce poison.
6658   // It can strip off addrspacecast that do not change bit representation as
6659   // well. We believe that such addrspacecast is equivalent to no-op.
6660   auto *StrippedV = V->stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation();
